    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the roster as our premier asset. With an elite efficiency score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and a prime leadoff spot against Teng, making him the cornerstone of our lineup. Following him, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (73.86) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (72.97) are must-starts; the latter gains significant value from a favorable matchup against Holmes, whose 4.43 xERA and exploitable profile provide a 10% skill advantage for our hitters. We are also capitalizing on high-ceiling situational matchups for **Josh Lowe** and **Kyle Tucker**, both of whom are projected for strong outputs as they face a weak arm in Martin, with **Josh Lowe** specifically benefiting from a 17% SP skill boost.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a score of 52.47. While **Josh Jung** offers consistent plate presence, he was edged out by the superior efficiency scores of **Nolan Schanuel** and **Dominic Smith** in this specific context; **Nolan Schanuel** remains in the utility slot due to the high-probability volume expected against the favorable Martin matchup. We remain cautious regarding **Brady House** (57.34); while his platoon splits are promising, the opposing pitcher's ability to hold runners to a 53% SB rate suppresses his overall utility in our scarcity-focused build. No severe weather risks are currently flagged, but monitor **Drake Baldwin** and **Andy Pages** for any late-breaking lineup shifts, as their lower-mid-tier scores make them the first candidates for benching if weather conditions deteriorate or defensive substitutions are announced.",
